/**

\page install How To Install

This is a guide about installing PyLinda.

\section getting Getting The Code

The code is available from the PyLinda website at <a href="http://www-users.cs.york.ac.uk/~aw/pylinda">http://www-users.cs.york.ac.uk/~aw/pylinda</a>.

Once you've downloaded the tarball extract it and run setup.py with <i>install</i> as the argument. Run <code>python setup.py --help</code> for more detailed installation options.

\code
tar -xzf linda-0.2.tar.gz
cd linda-0.2
python setup.py install
\endcode

On Linux this will install PyLinda to your Python packages directory, the linda_server.py script to /usr/bin and the documentation and examples to /usr/share/pylinda.

*/
